## Testing Standards

### Test Pyramid

- **Unit (70%)** — ALL business logic, utilities, hooks
- **Integration (20%)** — ALL API endpoints, service interactions
- **E2E (10%)** — Critical user flows

### Test Rules

- Required for ALL business logic, utilities, hooks, API endpoints
- Meaningful descriptions: "should [expected] when [condition]"
- Test edge cases: empty, null, boundary, concurrent access
- Test error scenarios: network failures, invalid inputs, permission errors
- Never skip tests — `.skip()` only with documented, tracked issue
- Mock at boundaries, never inside business logic
- Test files mirror source file structure

---

## Build & Deployment

- **Bundle size:** report if initial load exceeds 500KB
- **Source maps:** dev enabled, production disabled (unless error tracking)
- **Tree shaking:** must be effective — no dead code in production
- **Code splitting:** route-based and component-based
- **Health check endpoints:** `/health`, `/readiness`, `/liveness`
- **Graceful shutdown:** SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers
- **Zero-downtime deployments:** handle in-flight requests during shutdown
- **Rollback strategy:** documented for every deployment

---

## UI/UX Standards

- **Mobile-first** with consistent breakpoint system
- **Touch targets:** minimum 44x44px
- **Accessibility:** WCAG 2.1 AA minimum — alt text, keyboard nav, semantic HTML, 4.5:1 contrast, ARIA attributes
- **Performance:** Lighthouse > 90, LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
- **Animations:** 150-300ms micro-interactions, `prefers-reduced-motion` respected, use `transform`/`opacity`
- **Loading states:** skeleton screens or progress indicators for async ops
- **Error states:** user-friendly messages with recovery actions
- **Empty states:** meaningful guidance when no data available

